<h2>What Features Does Stocky Swap Include?</h2>
<p>Stocky Swap covers the core inventory management capabilities most Shopify stores use day-to-day:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Real-time order logging</strong> — every paid order captured instantly in Google Sheets</li>
  <li><strong>SKU-level tracking</strong> — product title, variant, SKU, and quantity per order</li>
  <li><strong>Stock depletion tracking</strong> — subtract sold quantities against your opening stock levels</li>
  <li><strong>Low-stock alerts</strong> — automatic Make.com email trigger when a SKU hits your threshold</li>
  <li><strong>Revenue per SKU</strong> — gross revenue calculated per product line automatically</li>
  <li><strong>Fulfilment status sync</strong> — order status updated in Sheets when Shopify marks fulfilled</li>
</ul>
<p>Stocky Swap does not replicate Stocky's demand forecasting module or direct supplier purchase order creation. For stores that relied heavily on those features, Inventory Planner is the closest paid alternative at $99/month.</p>

<h2>Should You Pay for a Stocky Replacement?</h2>
<p>For most Shopify stores under 500 orders per month, Stocky Swap provides everything needed at $0. The paid alternatives — Linnworks, Skubana, Inventory Planner — are designed for multi-warehouse, multi-channel operations with dozens of suppliers. If you ran Stocky, you almost certainly don't need a $449/month WMS.</p>
<p>The recommendation is: <strong>migrate to Stocky Swap first</strong>. It deploys in 4 minutes. If you hit its limits (high-volume multi-SKU stores with complex forecasting needs), evaluate paid alternatives from there.</p>

